Test V: Exclusion Criteria Consistency
H&K Test V injects a monetary policy distractor into documents and adds a corresponding exclusion rule to the codebook, then tests all four combinations of (normal/modified) x (document/codebook). The model should only apply the exclusion when both the trigger and the rule are present (combo 4).


Show code
